\pard\nowidctlpar {\cf0\f0 It was a boring Tuesday evening, me and my friend Linda were stuck in our dorm room thinking of ways to kill the boredom we were feeling.\uc0{\u8220}Aaarrrrghh\uc0{\u8230}I\uc0{\u8217}m so bored, I hate this feeling,\uc0{\u8221} I said.\uc0{\u8220}Same girl, same,\uc0{\u8221} replied Linda.Me, Linda and Rita were all at University and shared pretty much everything, from the same dorm rooms to the same course we did at University. We became best friends in the first semester and became unbreakable since then.Unlike us who loved partying and always sought opportunities to go out dancing, Rita was a church girl and she did not go out as much.On this fateful day like any other weekend we had failed to find someone to take us out partying hence the boredom.After hours of frustration, sleep and yawns, finally our friend Kemi came to our dorm room with the best news our teenage ears had yearned to hear over five hours ago.Kemi was a friend we met at campus when we first joined, she had technically finished university but remained back because she had not graduated yet.\uc0{\u8220}Giiiiiiirrrrrllllllsssss !!!\uc0{\u8221} She screamed running into our dorm room with her red stilettos.\uc0{\u8220}Kemiiiiiii!!!\uc0{\u8221} The three of us screamed while running to embrace her.\uc0{\u8220}I have good news girls, we are going out to party!!\uc0{\u8221} Kemi screamed again with excitement.We all screamed in excitement too except for Rita of course,\uc0{\u8220}Ooh my God, let me get my shoes ready for the dance floor,\uc0{\u8221} Linda said while running to the wardrobe in the corner of the square room.\uc0{\u8220}So these guys are filthy rich and they asked me to come with some friends so they can spend some money, drinks, food and everything else is all on their bill!\uc0{\u8221} Kemi said.\uc0{\u8220}Yeeyyyy, I was so bored, finally Kemi the savior is here with the best news ever, let me get dressed and put some make up on,\uc0{\u8221} I replied with so much vigor.All this while in our excitement, Rita was in the corner watching in what I would call pity for us.\uc0{\u8220}Linda, Aber, do you girls even know the guys Kemi is talking about ?\uc0{\u8221} Rita finally broke her silence.\uc0{\u8220}We don\uc0{\u8217}t have to know the men Rita, they just have to buy us drinks that\uc0{\u8217}s all, grow up already!\uc0{\u8221} Linda replied with frustration in her voice.\uc0{\u8220}I still think it\uc0{\u8217}s a bad idea honestly, Aber please don\uc0{\u8217}t go, we can watch a movie and stay in the dorm tonight,\uc0{\u8221} Rita said while turning to me for a change of heart, but I was already too excited and I just wanted to go out.\uc0{\u8220}How about we do that tomorrow? And I\uc0{\u8217}ll call and text you throughout the night to show you that we are okay, besides don\uc0{\u8217}t you trust Kemi ?\uc0{\u8221} I asked.\uc0{\u8220}I have no words for this church girl honestly, you are so boring,\uc0{\u8221} Kemi responded with a mean dead stare at Rita.\uc0{\u8220}My bad Kemi, I did not mean to offend any of you, enjoy your night out,\uc0{\u8221} Rita responded.We continued to get ready and an hour later a Range Rover came to pick us up.\uc0{\u8220}Aber this is going to be the best night ever I can feel it already,\uc0{\u8221} Linda said to me while squeezing my hand with excitement.We walked to the car and met two men inside,\uc0{\u8220}Hello, you ladies look so beautiful, Kemi indeed your friends are beautiful.\uc0{\u8221} One of the men said when we sat in the back seat.\uc0{\u8220}Thank you,\uc0{\u8221} we all replied in unison.\uc0{\u8220}This is Aber and Linda,\uc0{\u8221} Kemi said.\uc0{\u8220}Sorry about my impolite manners, I went straight to complimenting your beauty without introducing ourselves. I am Paul and this is John,\uc0{\u8221} said Paul.\uc0{\u8220}Hey Paul, Hey John,\uc0{\u8221} I replied.\uc0{\u8220}You are so beautiful I\uc0{\u8217}m losing focus on the road already,\uc0{\u8221} John giggled as he drove dangerously fast. We laughed and drove to the restaurant, the conversations were amazing. We spoke about school, businesses, houses and cars.The restaurant we went to was so beautiful and classy, they let us order for whatever food or drinks we wanted.\uc0{\u8220}I wish Rita was outgoing, now she is missing all this,\uc0{\u8221} I said as I took a picture of the food to send to Rita,\uc0{\u8220}So girls, what bar are we heading to now that we are almost done with the first phase that is food,\uc0{\u8221} Paul asked while looking at Kemi.\uc0{\u8220}The Groove is the best place in town right now, I think we should go and check it out, who knows maybe they have a great Dj as well because we girls love to dance, don\uc0{\u8217}t we girls? \uc0{\u8220} Kemi asked while looking at us.\uc0{\u8220}Of course, I just want to dance the night away and this food I have stuffed myself with,\uc0{\u8221} Linda replied with a wide smile on her face.The men paid the bill and we walked to the car and drove off to The Groove. It was indeed a new place in town and only VIPs were known to be the only ones frequenting the place which meant it was a very expensive bar.When we got to the bar, Kemi asked us to go to the bathroom as the men got us a booth and some drinks, we followed her to the bathroom while dancing to the music that was playing in the bar.\uc0{\u8220}So girls, you know these guys like you already and they have a lot of money, they can buy you anything you want and they could even take you for vacations if you accept them,\uc0{\u8221} Kemi said to us.\uc0{\u8220}What do you mean by accept them?\uc0{\u8221} I asked in confusion because I thought we just came out to party.\uc0{\u8220}Grow up Aber, Kemi already said the guys like us so what is there not to understand?\uc0{\u8221} Linda replied but I knew she was already tipsy from the restaurant.\uc0{\u8220}Aber, John likes you and maybe when you both get drunk you might end up at his place, who knows how the night will end, come on don\uc0{\u8217}t worry it\uc0{\u8217}s not even important if u don\uc0{\u8217}t want him then nothing will happen, let\uc0{\u8217}s just go back and have fun, they must be waiting,\uc0{\u8221} Kemi said to me.I brushed it off because I had come to have fun and dance, not to hook up. We walked out of the bathroom to the booth where we found bottles of champagne and black label all waiting for us on the table.We joined in with screams or excitement and started to toast and drink while dancing. The DJ was playing the best music, perhaps it was just alcohol making me feel that way.At midnight the DJs usually announce birthdays and as the music went down, John froze, he didn\uc0{\u8217}t move nor blink, he just had a dead stare.\uc0{\u8220}John! John!\uc0{\u8221} Paul tried to shake him to no avail.\uc0{\u8220}So sorry this happens sometimes but he will get back to being himself in a short while, don\uc0{\u8217}t you worry.\uc0{\u8221} Paul chuckled under his breath.I was so terrified,\uc0{\u8220}What does he mean by he will get back to himself ?\uc0{\u8221}\uc0{\u8220}Is he possessed?\uc0{\u8221}\uc0{\u8220}Is it an illness?\uc0{\u8221} I thought to myself as I walked away to the bathroom.}\par
